// VER-025 Palette Slots - expected lookup texels.
//
// One reference texel per non-empty, non-comment line.  Each line is a
// 36-bit UQ1.8 RGBA value packed as `{R[8:0], G[8:0], B[8:0], A[8:0]}`
// rendered as 9 hex characters (zero-padded; the high nibble is unused
// because the value is 36 bits wide).  `$readmemh` consumes the lines
// below in order; `//` line comments and blank lines are skipped.
//
// The same file is consumed by the digital twin's `gs-tex-palette-lut`
// integration test which runs the identical scenario sequence against
// the Rust model and asserts byte-for-byte equality.  Any divergence
// between this file, the Verilator testbench output, and the twin
// output is a real bug -- fix the RTL or the twin.
//
// Procedural pattern used to derive the seed-dependent reference
// values (matches `texture_palette_tb::ref_blob_pattern_uq18` and the
// `gs-tex-palette-lut::test_helpers::seed_pattern` Rust helper):
//
//   For seed `s` at palette entry `e`, quadrant `q`:
//     R8 = e ^ s
//     G8 = ((e + q) & 0xFF) ^ rotnib8(s)
//     B8 = ((e * 3) & 0xFF) ^ q
//     A8 = ((e + 3*q) & 0xFF) ^ (~s & 0xFF)
//   where rotnib8(x) = ((x & 0x0F) << 4) | ((x & 0xF0) >> 4).
//
// The 9-bit promoted channel is `c9 = c8 + (c8 >> 7)` per DD-038.
//
// Lines are grouped per scenario.  Scenario 5 carries TWO palette
// lookups (pre/post index-cache invalidate) with identical expected
// values -- the test is that the palette LUT is unaffected by the
// `tex0_cache_inv` strobe.
//
// SCENARIO 1: dual-slot use (slot0 sampler0, slot1 sampler1)
411f98e7e
0c3a18ee8
// SCENARIO 2: mid-frame palette reload (pre, post)
21af904c0
7c3dd040b
// SCENARIO 3: quadrant exhaustive (NW, NE, SW, SE) at slot 0 idx 0x42
558444433
5e110aa66
669dd129a
6f3bde20f
// SCENARIO 4: MIRROR-wrap quadrant swap (re-uses S3 overrides)
558444433
5e110aa66
5e110aa66
558444433
669dd129a
6f3bde20f
// SCENARIO 5: cache invalidate semantics (pre, post)
411f98e7e
